abstract: “I am the poster boy for doing everything offensive. I’ve done insane things. But everything I did, I make no apologies for, because I was trying to entertain people.”

headline_main: Howard Stern Says He’s Changed. How Much?

abstract: At a relatively subdued “Make America Great Again” rally on Wednesday night, the president riffed on familiar themes, like the “fake news media” and Hillary Clinton.
snippet: At a relatively subdued “Make America Great Again” rally on Wednesday night, the president riffed on familiar themes, like the “fake news media” and Hillary Clinton.
lead_paragraph: PANAMA CITY BEACH, Fla. — President Trump on Wednesday brought his amped-up roadshow to this spring break playground on the Florida gulf coast, demanding that Democrats stop the “nonsense” of investigating him, mocking Democratic presidential candidates like Joe Biden and Pete Buttigieg, and joking about staying in the White House for another decade.

abstract: Ms. Klobuchar, in a town hall event, called herself a “proven progressive,” while also appealing to Fox’s conservative viewers with her bipartisan record.
snippet: Ms. Klobuchar, in a town hall event, called herself a “proven progressive,” while also appealing to Fox’s conservative viewers with her bipartisan record.
lead_paragraph: Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota defended her presidential candidacy as one that could appeal to both moderate and liberal voters, calling herself a “proven progressive” and casting her record as one of bipartisan accomplishment.

headline_print_headline: Calling Herself ‘Progressive,’ Klobuchar Tries to Widen Appeal on Fox

abstract: There is no good reason to put yet another man in the White House.
snippet: There is no good reason to put yet another man in the White House.
lead_paragraph: According to pollsters and political reporters, a dispiriting dynamic has taken hold of the early stages of the Democratic presidential primary: Voters are discounting female candidates as unelectable.

abstract: Many other countries make it easy for incarcerated people to vote.
snippet: Many other countries make it easy for incarcerated people to vote.
lead_paragraph: As the Democratic candidates debate whether current and former prisoners should be allowed to vote, it’s worth recalling that many other countries make it easy for incarcerated people to do it.

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: Nearly every candidate can stake a claim as the most electable. It just depends on how you think the election will be won.
